---
import BaseLayout from 'src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            color: #333;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
        }

        .container {
            width: 80%;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 30px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #fff;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 36px;
            color: #2c3e50;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        p {
            font-size: 18px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .intro {
            font-size: 20px;
            color: #555;
            font-weight: bold;
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 28px;
            color: #34495e;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        ul, ol {
            margin: 15px 0;
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        code {
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            padding: 5px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-size: 1.1em;
            color: #c0392b;
        }

        .code-example {
            background-color: #ecf0f1;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin: 15px 0;
            font-family: monospace;
        }

        .highlight {
            color: #e74c3c;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        footer {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 30px;
            padding-top: 10px;
            border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
            color: #777;
            font-size: 14px;
        }
    </style>
    <div class="container">
        <a href="/bloglist" style="display: inline-block; margin-bottom: 20px; text-decoration: none; color: #3498db;">&larr; Back</a>
        <header>
            <h1>Mastering SQL Databases</h1>
            <p class="intro">Understand SQL queries, database design, and optimization techniques for managing data efficiently.</p>
        </header>

        <section>
            <h2>What is SQL?</h2>
            <p>Think of SQL as a universal language for talking to databases - it's like being able to ask your digital filing cabinet exactly what you want! Whether you're building an app, a website, or analyzing data, SQL is your trusty sidekick.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Your First SQL Query</h2>
            <div class="code-example">
                <code><pre>{`-- This is how you get all users from a table
SELECT * FROM users;

-- Get specific columns
SELECT first_name, last_name, email FROM users;`}</pre></code>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Creating Your Database</h2>
            <p>Let's build a simple database for a bookstore:</p>
            <div class="code-example">
                <code><pre>{`CREATE TABLE books (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    title VARCHAR(100),
    author VARCHAR(50),
    price DECIMAL(10,2),
    published_date DATE
);`}</pre></code>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Fun with Data!</h2>
            <p>Here's how to add some books to your database:</p>
            <div class="code-example">
                <code><pre>{`INSERT INTO books (id, title, author, price)
VALUES (1, 'The SQL Adventure', 'Jane Doe', 29.99);

-- Get all expensive books
SELECT title, author 
FROM books 
WHERE price > 20.00;`}</pre></code>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Joining Tables - Like Puzzle Pieces</h2>
            <p>Connecting different tables is where SQL really shines:</p>
            <div class="code-example">
                <code><pre>{`SELECT books.title, authors.name
FROM books
JOIN authors ON books.author_id = authors.id;`}</pre></code>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Cool SQL Tricks</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>üîç <strong>Finding Patterns:</strong> Use LIKE with % wildcards</li>
                <li>üìä <strong>Grouping Data:</strong> GROUP BY with aggregate functions</li>
                <li>üîÑ <strong>Sorting Results:</strong> ORDER BY for organization</li>
                <li>üéØ <strong>Filtering Groups:</strong> HAVING for group conditions</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Best Practices</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Always backup your database</li>
                <li>Use meaningful table and column names</li>
                <li>Index frequently searched columns</li>
                <li>Write clean, formatted queries</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Practice Projects</h2>
            <p>Try building these simple projects to practice:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>üìù Todo List Database</li>
                <li>üìö Personal Library Manager</li>
                <li>üë• Contact Management System</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <footer>
            <p>&copy; 2024 Learn2Code | Empowering beginners to dive into programming</p>
        </footer>
    </div>
</BaseLayout>
